                            <comment id="12752875" author="bluk" created="Wed, 9 Sep 2009 03:05:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve gone ahead and changed the toleration for &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;*&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt; to a &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;*/*&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt; since some JDKs and other clients have an Accept header with &quot;*&quot; in it by default and there&apos;s no chance to change that code.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On some thought, for changing the &quot;text/&quot; to &quot;text/*&quot; or other invalid accept headers, the right response may be a 400 response instead of the current 500 (or skipping invalid media types).  I&apos;m leaning more towards the 400 instead of encouraging bad behavior.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12752883" author="hudson" created="Wed, 9 Sep 2009 03:40:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Wink-Trunk-JDK1.5 #136 (See &lt;a href=&quot;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Wink-Trunk-JDK1.5/136/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Wink-Trunk-JDK1.5/136/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    Tolerate &quot;*&quot; Accept header value&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See []&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12753276" author="hudson" created="Wed, 9 Sep 2009 21:39:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Wink-Trunk-JDK1.5 #140 (See &lt;a href=&quot;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Wink-Trunk-JDK1.5/140/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Wink-Trunk-JDK1.5/140/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    Send a 400 when Accept header has invalid types&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See []&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12753609" author="bluk" created="Thu, 10 Sep 2009 13:11:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Throws a 400 on illegal media type accept headers except for the &quot;&lt;b&gt;&quot; case which turns it into a &quot;&lt;/b&gt;/*&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
